 weight on the Reaver will sap all my endurance during a fight?  Stonebladed axe of dismay runs for 14k, its kinda expensive but is it worth the price?  <br><br>Btw, Im lvl 45 with nice gear ac wise, and chitin hand wraps as haste.  Thanks in advance.<br><br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uemiliaeq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>EmiliaEQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 287<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/27/02 11:49:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3724.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Damage Wise 2 handers for 8kish?  Not MT</span><hr size=1> Reaver sux, NEVER EVER get one (non magical)<br><br>Any 2H with a 0.9 to 1.0 ratio will do.<br>The best of course is the 44/44 hp75 axe (15-20kish on Karana)<br><br>Dont get Velium/Axe of Agression/ToD (for pure DPS)<br>(tod is an utility weapon)<br><br>My proposition :<br><br>1) Savage Stone Axe (nice ratio and fast)<br>2) Black Acrylia Halbert (nice ratio good proc)<br>3) Stonebladed Axe of Dismay (insane ratio)<br><br>45/44 = primal ... so you can see why the 44/44 axe owns. <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=5132"/A><img src= http://members.cox.net/johnj1/eq/emiliast.jpg></BR>     </p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uemiliaeq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>EmiliaEQ</A> at: 8/27/02 11:50:49 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ugrimmlokk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimmlokk</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://grimmlokk.homestead.com/files/icon.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 872<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/27/02 11:55:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3724.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://grimmlokk.homestead.com/files/spinhead2.gif?flezbwidth=30&flezbheight=41? WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Damage Wise 2 handers for 8kish?  Not MT</span><hr size=1>  Pretty sure all the CT weapons are not equippable before 51.<br><br> When you are 51 though another one to look for is the Tae Ew War Maul. 33/36 65hp 2HB. And cheap. Have seen for 4k or so regularly. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6122" target="_blank"><img src=http://grimmlokk.homestead.com/files/newface2.gif></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=rolsdar>rolsdar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 90<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/28/02 1:04:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3724.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Damage Wise 2 handers for 8kish? Not MT</span><hr size=1> As your lvl 45  wont be able to use the stonebladed axe yet, so i would get the black acrylia halbred as it has a recommened lvl of 45.<br><br>I consistently hit for 150+ and with buffs this thing rocks hitting in the 200 constantly. The proc on it is a 45hp lifetap, which although not that great can be usefull over the length of a fight as it procs quite often .When u hit 51 get the stonebladed axe. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukilaara.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kilaara</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 148<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/28/02 4:59:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3724.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.elchtom.de/Fantasy/f49.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Damage Wise 2 handers for 8kish? Not MT</span><hr size=1> The Truncheon of Doom has 33/44 so its ratio is not the winner. But when the proc (50% Slow) comes you will have a better time. <p><p><p><table border="0" cellpadding="3" ><tr><td><table border="4"  style="background-image:url(http://members.tripod.de/Shabaza/back.jpg); "> <tr> <td  align="center" width="86" nowrap> <font size="2" face="Times New Roman"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4552"style=Color:"cccc00">Kilaara<br>Drachenfliege</a><br><font size="1" face="Arial" color=silver><i>Gnome <br>Warlady</i></font></td><td align="center"width="88" nowrap><font size="2" face="Times New Roman"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=175753"style=Color:"cccc00">Nessaya<br>Schattenfinger</a><br><font size="1" face="Arial" color=silver><i>Barbarian <br>Rogue</i></font></td><td align="center" width="81" nowrap><font size="2" face="Times New Roman"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=186275"style=Color:"cccc00">Kilashandra<br>Rhee</a><br><font size="1" face="Arial" color=silver><i>Gnome <br>Heretic</i></font></td><td align="center" width="83" nowrap><font size="2" face="Times New Roman"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=245267"style=Color:"cccc00">Nimashandra<br>Rhee</a><br><font size="1" face="Arial" color=silver><i>Halfling <br>Vicar</i></font></td><td align="center" width="66" nowrap><font size="2" face="Times New Roman"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=196609"style=Color:"cccc00">Crysania<br>L'Epicea</a><br><font size="1" 