0 ratio) 2Hander.<br><br>After that, dont even bother with weapons again.<br><br>Only willsaper+ will be on any assistance.<br>And you wont see these before a loooong loooong time.<br><br>That 44/44 axe has the same ratio as primal, and beats half<br>of NToV 2handers.<br><br>Once you get it, you will be set for weapons for a few months.<br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uemiliaeq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>EmiliaEQ</A> at: 8/28/02 6:39:42 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukhumak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Khumak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/28/02 2:58:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3724.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ok</span><hr size=1> If you can get the 44/44 for 8k jump on it.  Cheapest I have seen is 12k and I resold it for 20k (then picked up another later for 15k).  I'd say for 8k your best bet is probably the 33/36 axe. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=85547>Khumak</a><br>60 Warrior<br>Mith Marr<br>(Imperial Guardians)</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/usamdech.showPublicProfile?language=EN>samdech</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/29/02 2:00:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3724.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Related question</span><hr size=1> Good information here... I have a question though.<br><br>In terms of damage (I'm currently level 5<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> , how do these 2 compare:<br><br>Frostbringer (12/22 frostbite) / LSoEE (16-21/29)<br>vs.<br>Tae Ew War Maul (2HB 33/36)<br><br>The reason I'm asking is that I bought a ToD (and boy I'm glad I did) but swapping it with two 1 handers after it procs becomes annoying after a while. I was thinking about getting a war maul to swap with ToD. <br><br>Also I'm not considering aggro issues here.<br><br>Many thanks in advance <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uheka01.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Heka01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/29/02 4:31:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3724.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Related question</span><hr size=1> One idea is have good relations with the guilds that kill the Dain. He drops the axe quite often and when we kill him we invariably call in people to loot his no drop 2h. With you having a druid partner you can be in the pit in under 5 mins and it's a decent weapon. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showPrevMessage?topicID=3724.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showNextMessage?topicID=3724.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><